Last week, we trapped a stray dog thinking it was our neighborhood friend that we had been feeding for the last year or so. Since she was obviously still lactating, we released her the next day attached to a long leash to see if she would lead us to her puppies. And guess where she led us to? A slaughterhouse!! Momma ended up being a random loose dog that had ventured out from a dog meat farm tucked away in the mountains. Hiding in plain sight. Because all of them were barely fed (and if they were it was always food waste), some were forced to resort to cannibalism and others like Momma had to find scraps on the street to produce milk for her babies. We honestly can’t take on this many dogs, but after seeing the horrific conditions they had endured, we knew we couldn’t leave them behind, not even for another hour. We rescued 26 dogs that day, half of them puppies. RIP to the 2 dogs who died a death that was absolutely avoidable. Fly high, angels.

⠀
안녕하십니까! 동물권혁명 캣치독팀입니다.
캣치독팀에서 주관하는 스크린 캠페인 집회가
12일에서 일주일 뒤로 한 오는 19일.
드디어 시작하게 됩니다.

유통 경로를 통해 국민들에게 소비를 꾀하는
이 부패한 실상의 과정을 낱낱이 보여드립니다.

인간이 지녀야 할 측은지심과 그 여지를
넘어서서 개 식용, 그 자체만으로도 관련
업자들이 국민의 인권을 기만하고 유린하고
있다는 사실을 알아야 합니다.

수요를 대폭 줄이는 효과를 얻습니다.

소비자들은 이야기합니다.
먹는 것에 대한 자유를 침해하냐고.
캣치독팀은 이야기합니다.
이미 그 자유가 그들에게서 유린 당하고 있다고.
⠀
닫혀져있던 블라인드를 열고
국민 여러분들과 함께 봅니다.
⠀
자. 이제는 다른 각도로 접근합시다!
⠀
인권유린!
개 식용 철폐!
대국민 사기 집단!

개 식용 관련 업자들 멈추지 않으면
멈추게 하겠습니다.

Hello,
We are Team.Cat’chDog, an animal rights and rescue organization based in South Korea.
We had planned for a nationwide large-scale monitor campaign to kick off on the 12th, yet due to unforeseen circumstances had to push it back one week. 
We are excited to see a project we poured our hearts into finally come to fruition and are here to announce the grand launch.

The purpose of the campaign is two-fold. The first is to expose the highly unethical, unsanitary, and corrupt distribution networks of the dog meat trade. 
The second is to inform the general public how these dog meat farmers, merchants, and distributors deceive us and infringe on our rights. 

By bringing light to this darkness, we hope to depress the market. 

Consumers of dog-meat demand freedom to eat what they want. 
But to them we say, your freedom is already being compromised and undermined.

We want to open the curtains to a hidden world that was intentionally kept away from you. To do this, we are taking a different approach.

If you look at the way the system is designed, you will be able to see that it is being carried out in a way that is inherently an infringement on our rights.
Dog meat consumption must be terminated. These people have been grifting the South Korean people for decades.

If they won’t stop, we have no choice but to make them.

snippet.title: Your support for CatchDog Team saves lives
snippet.description:
Your support for Catchdog Team saves lives

We want to take this opportunity to thank our amazing supporters around the world.

Thanks to your PayPal donations, we have been able to save the lives of so many dogs.
Because of your critical support, these dogs can see another day to not only live but thrive. 

As you can see from our YouTube videos, this line of work is not easy. It is at times soul-crushing but too many dogs are suffering for us to falter. We will not stop until every last dog in Korea is saved from the dog meat industry. 

What is particularly horrific about this industry is the way dogs are treated and killed. They are kept in small cages and barely have room to stretch out their legs. Most are fed scraps and have limited access to water. And when they are dragged to their deaths, they are tortured in ways that even the darkest imaginations cannot fathom, and die a slow and painful death, often in front of their friends and family. 

Studies have proven that animal abusers are more likely to become serial killers. They start with small creatures that are unable to fight back. The number of cases that have skyrocketed in recent months and years is truly disturbing.

 As Mahatma Gandhi once said, “The greatness of a nation and its moral progress can be judged by the way its animals are treated.” It is deeply shameful and preposterous how we treat other animals. 

We see this as a problem that transcends national borders and cultures, and are painfully aware that change cannot happen overnight. And our actions barely make a dent in the grand scheme of things. But little things can add up to make a big difference. 

It is with this belief that we march onward. Whether it be one stray dog or a dog meat farm with hundreds of dogs, we will not turn a blind eye to any being that is suffering or needs our help. Humans are at the top of the food chain. We have the power to dominate but we do not have the right to plunder and destroy. We should be guardians, not masters. 

Without your support, this would not have been possible. We can’t thank you enough and hope that you will continue to open your hearts to animals in Korea.
